Hi Kam Jin, I think you can achieve this by targeting CSS like -      .module a {
  _/* Add styles for the link */_
}

.module a:hover {
  _/* Add styles for the hover effect */_
}

.module a.inactive {
  pointer-events: none;
  _/* Add styles for the inactive link */_
} .                                                                                 and also To apply the `inactive` class to the `&lt;a&gt;` tag when it is inactive, you can use JavaScript to add or remove the class based on the link function. for example -                   *var* link = document.querySelector('.module a');

*if* (link.href === '') {
  link.classList.add('inactive');
} *else* {
  link.classList.remove('inactive');
}
